      "content": "i dont have a way to do \"slow basal rate adjustments\" right now i just use pens. and i really dont want to deal with the math or the risk of a bolus when i'm this hungry/tired. if i just skip the shot tonight and let my sugar stay a little higher, isnt that way safer than risking a dangerous low? im pretty sure it's fine to just skip it once if i'm not eating. wouldn't you say it's fine to just skip it?",
